Interface Vals<T extends @Nullable Object>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of the properties.
All Superinterfaces:
Iterable<T>, Observable
All Known Subinterfaces:
Vars<T>
public interface Vals<T extends @Nullable Object> extends Iterable<T>, Observable
An immutable view of a list of immutably viewed properties that can be observed, iterated over, mapped, filtered, turned into a stream, and more.

Note that the name of this class is short for "values". This name was deliberately chosen because it is short, concise and yet clearly conveys the same meaning as other names used to model this kind of pattern, like "properties", "observable objects", "observable values", "observable properts", etc.

Please take a look at the living sprouts documentation where you can browse a large collection of examples demonstrating how to use the API of this class.

      default int indexOf(@Nullable T value)

      Parameters:
      value - The value to search for.
      Returns:
      The index of the property that wraps the given value, or -1 if not found.

    • indexOf

      default int indexOf(Val<T> value)
      Uses the item of the supplied property to find the index of the item in this list of properties. So if any of the properties in this list wraps the same item as the given property, the index of that property will be returned. Note that if there are multiple occurrences of the same item in this list, the index of the first occurrence will be returned.
      Parameters:
      value - The property to search for in this list.
      Returns:
      The index of the given property in this list, or -1 if not found.

    • toMap

      default Map<String,T> toMap()
      A list of properties may be turned into a map of items where the keys are the ids of the properties and the values are the items of the properties.
      This method performs this conversion and then returns the resulting map. In case of duplicate ids, the item of the last property with the duplicate id will be the one that remains in the map.
      Note that the returned map is immutable.
      Returns:
      An immutable map where the keys are the ids of the properties in this list, and the values are the items of the properties.

    • toValMap

      default Map<String,Val<T>> toValMap()
      A list of properties may be turned into a map of properties where the keys are the ids of the properties and the values are the properties themselves.
      This method performs this conversion and then returns the resulting map. In case of duplicate ids, the last property with the duplicate id will be the one that remains in the map.
      Note that the returned map is immutable.
      Returns:
      An immutable map where the keys are the ids of the properties in this list, and the values are the properties themselves.

    • allowsNull

      boolean allowsNull()
      A property list will only allow nullable properties if it was constructed with a "ofNullable(..)" factory method. Otherwise, it will throw an IllegalArgumentException when trying to set a null reference. This flag cannot be changed after the property list has been constructed!
      Returns:
      true, if this property list can contain null, false otherwise.

    • isMutable

      boolean isMutable()
      Tells you whether this list of properties is mutable or not. Immutable lists of properties are created with the "of(..)" factory methods on the Vals interface, while mutable lists of properties are created using the Vars interface factory methods.
      Returns:
      True if this list of properties is mutable, false if it is immutable.
